Downward inclination of the dipped-beam shall in all cases be produced in one of the following ways:
(a) By moving a control downwards or to the left;
(b) By rotating a control in a counter clockwise direction;
(c) By depressing a button (push-pull control).
If several buttons are used to adjust the beam, the button which gives the greatest downward inclination shall be installed to the left or below the button(s) for other dipped-beam positions.
